{"in": {"title": "Questing Lores", "subtitle": "<span id=\"tr_lore_id\">The Boy Who Could</span>", "lines": ["SCENE: https://lores.nonlinearmedia.org/res/mp3/misc/drone-settling-30s.mp3 (no wait)", "NARRATOR: Welcome. Today you'll be learning about the boy who could.", "NARRATOR: Often doubted, he learned to doubt himself. His mind a beautiful maze, he learned to solve it on his own.", "JACK: I knew The Boy Who Could, and one of his favorite things was to do this...", "JILL: (whisper) He whispered to himself the comforts for which he longed.", "JACK: (x-loud) HE YELLED the things which he knew all too well, but was beginning to forget.", "JILL: (soft) And always, a balanced head on his shoulders, he made decisions in a soft voice.", "JACK: He learned the strength of the weapon which he knew to be his own brain.", "NARRATOR: With it, he could solve any problem, learn any idea, create any construct, and realize any dream.", "SCENE: https://lores.nonlinearmedia.org/res/mp3/misc/random-foley-2s.mp3", "NARRATOR: That was a cool sound.", "SCENE: https://lores.nonlinearmedia.org/res/mp3/misc/eerie-music-8s.mp3 (no wait)", "NARRATOR: Another cool sound to be the background of this one!", "NARRATOR: Anyways, The Boy Who Could was a glorious specimen. But he took a while to become himself.", "JILL: He grew up surrounded by the enemy, the Non-Believers. Not like a religion in the slightest, btw.", "JACK: But his own belief, strengthened by the likes of H. Potter, P. Jackson, N. Uzumaki, and the countless others...", "JILL: ...it held strong, and with it he fought off the enemies inside his soul.", "JACK: You're right, Jill. He went on to become the greatest, most powerful hero of any story ever told.", "JILL: It's funny, Jack, because in the end, he was just a normal, Indian boy living in America with anxiety, depression, and a good start in life.", "JACK: But he became more than himself, Jill. He transformed, he found love, he found success, and he even tortured himself enough that he finally, at the end of it all, found happiness.", "JILL: And that's why his story is told. Because his \"happily forever after\" was a real one. Not a fictitious ending left out of a novel.", "JACK: Because he was real.", "JILL: It's funny, he would have loved to see this. An ending written like the ending a player sees once they beat Minecraft. He thought that was the coolest thing ever.", "JACK: If there's a heaven, I know he's smiling down on us for helping transcribe it.", "NARRATOR: The most beautiful part, in my opinion, though, is that the story isn't finished. It's still, to this day, being written. By you.", "NARRATOR: By every one of you...", "SCENE: https://lores.nonlinearmedia.org/res/mp3/misc/cool-cosmic-sounding-5s.mp3"], "speaker_map": {"NARRATOR": "Joanna", "SCENE": "Joanna", "JILL": "Ivy", "JACK": "Justin"}}, "out": {"cache_id": "4f99db49df81fbefb05c9f634f6d82ec", "audio_objects": [["https://lores.nonlinearmedia.org/res/mp3/misc/drone-settling-30s.mp3", 1], ["77a0734fa9264122d40f8318267d6afa-welcome--today-you-ll-be----", 0], ["bfca3928fd56ebad6ded10a782bb005d-often-doubted--he-learned---", 0], ["f6e42b693699e37d8ee1ee8c9137cc43-i-knew-the-boy-who-could----", 0], ["1c3d2bc93d80c5a50aa3aba87dae8e32--he-whispered-to-himself----", 0], ["7455fe3ed6e1b109357c315d86abe8f2--he-yelled-the-things-whi---", 0], ["e71c8fecbdd03cb17eb4dc44016c95cc--and-always--a-balanced-h---", 0], ["9d441edefcb9c035cfca7eed43471e4e-he-learned-the-strength-o---", 0], ["40ba2d710480baacfc44a430cdda999b-with-it--he-could-solve-a---", 0], ["https://lores.nonlinearmedia.org/res/mp3/misc/random-foley-2s.mp3", 0], ["5a305f1c9c38cfe9ebe6c3622acf97f5-that-was-a-cool-sound-", 0], ["https://lores.nonlinearmedia.org/res/mp3/misc/eerie-music-8s.mp3", 1], ["166b1b73a2f8805237da11d16a0b8ca3-another-cool-sound-to-be----", 0], ["fd318325afe40937e87c3ff97460792d-anyways--the-boy-who-coul---", 0], ["cf0dac8ac59cf932eca96229f7274689-he-grew-up-surrounded-by----", 0], ["c930eb11ae10ac2c91